an.Order.PreservesSup.frameClosure\">frameClosure</a> <span class=\"fn\">op</span> <span class=\"fn\">k</span> <span class=\"fn\">fun (<span class=\"fn\">a</span> : <span class=\"fn\">β</span>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">op</span> <span class=\"fn\">F</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">Q</span> <span class=\"fn\">a</span>)</span></span></span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The frame rule, internalized: for a family of `Sup`-preserving operators `op r` whose resources\ncompose by `comp` with the action law `op (comp r r') = op r ∘ op r'`, and any post-transformer `k`,\n`op F (frameClosure op k Q) ⊑ frameClosure op k (fun a => op F (Q a))`. ","docLink":"./Std/Internal/Do/Order/PreservesSup.html#Lean.Order.PreservesSup.frameClosure_frames","kind":"theorem","line":75,"name":"Lean.Order.PreservesSup.frameClosure_frames","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Std/Internal/Do/Order/PreservesSup.lean#L75-L91"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">noncomputable def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Internal/Do/Order/PreservesSup.html#Lean.Order.PreservesSup.frameClosure\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Order</span>.<span class=\"name\">PreservesSup</span>.<span class=\"name\">frameClosure</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Internal/Order/Basic.html#Lean.Order.CompleteLattice\">CompleteLattice</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">R</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> v}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">β</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> w}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">op</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">R</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">k</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">β</span> → <span class=\"fn\">α</span>)</span> → <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">Q</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">β</span> → <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">α</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The **frame closure** of a post-transformer `k` with respect to a family of `Sup`-preserving\noperators `op r`: the meet over all resources `r` of the `r`-upper-adjoint of `k` framed by `r`. It\ninternalizes the frame rule into any `k` (see `frameClosure_frames`), with no assumption on `k`. A\nweakest precondition built as `frameClosure op (fun Q => bwp x Q E)` satisfies the `op`-frame rule by\nconstruction. ","docLink":"./Std/Internal/Do/Order/PreservesSup.html#Lean.Order.PreservesSup.frameClosure","kind":"def","line":66,"name":"Lean.Order.PreservesSup.frameClosure","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Std/Internal/Do/Order/PreservesSup.lean#L66-L73"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Internal/Do/Order/PreservesSup.html#Lean.Order.PreservesSup.map_mono\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Order</span>.<span class=\"name\">PreservesSup</span>.<span class